    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/vr-stiffness-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean construct stiffness: 142.3 N/mm (SD 4.1). Experimental mean: 138.7 N/mm (SD 6.8). Normalised error E/uval = 0.61, within the pre-established acceptance bound of 1.96. UQ campaign (Morris screening + first-order Sobol indices, 512 runs) identified Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus as the dominant sensitivity parameter (S1=0.47), followed by screw-rod interface friction coefficient (S1=0.29). Parametric uncertainty does not alter the pass/fail outcome."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/vr-yield-force-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean yield force: 312.5 N (SD 9.3). Experimental mean: 307.1 N (SD 14.2). Normalised error E/uval = 0.44, within acceptance bound. Sobol total-effect indices from the UQ campaign confirm that cortical bone density contributes negligibly (ST=0.04) to yield-force variance, supporting the simplification of uniform bone block properties in the validation model."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/vr-force-40mm-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean force at 40 mm: 487.2 N (SD 18.6). Experimental mean: 479.4 N (SD 22.1). Normalised error E/uval = 0.39, within acceptance bound. The UQ campaign confirmed that model predictions remain within acceptance bounds across the 5th–95th percentile range of all sampled input parameters, providing additional confidence in the robustness of the FEA framework."
    }
  ],
